Foot and mouth disease, Algeria
---------------------------------
Information received on 19 Aug 2014 from Dr Ahmed Chawky Karim Boughalem, Directeur des Services Veterinaires, Services Veterinaires, Ministere de l'Agriculture et du Developpement Rural, Alger, Algeria

Summary
Report type: Follow-up report No. 2
Date of start of the event: 23 Jul 2014
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 25 Jul 2014
Report date: 19 Aug 2014
Date submitted to OIE: 19 Aug 2014
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 1999
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Foot and mouth disease virus
Serotype: O
Nature of diagnosis: Clinical, Laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to: a defined zone within the country. [Why not the entire country? - Mod.AS]
Related reports: Immediate notification (27 Jul 2014)
Follow-up report No. 1 (7 Aug 2014)
Follow-up report No. 2 (19 Aug 2014)

New outbreaks (154)
[For the details pertaining to each of the 154 reported outbreaks (location name, number of susceptible, clinical cases and mortalities) and a map presenting their respective locations, please refer to the source URL. Notably, all outbreaks refer to cattle, mostly kept in small units (less than 10 animals). Only 7 holdings included 20 animals or more; the largest, 33 cattle. - Mod.AS]

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 154
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 932 / 341 / 3 / 0 / 929
Goats / 80 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 80
Sheep / 132 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 132

Outbreak statistics (rates apparent, expressed in percentages)
Species / morbidity rate / mortality rate / case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 36.59 / 0.32 / 0.88 / 100.00
Goats / 0.00 / 0.00 / ** / 100.00
Sheep / 0.00 / 0.00 / ** / 100.00

*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Illegal movement of animals
Epidemiological comments
Other control measures:
- closing of livestock markets in all wilayahs in the country,
- ban on movement of animals at national level,
- stamping out of all animals in the outbreaks,
- investigations strengthened.

Control measures
Measures applied: Samping out; Movement control inside the country; Screening/Vaccination in response to the outbreak(s); Disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s), No treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied: no other measures

